          <blockquote class="quote">
            "I take it with ibuprofen during heavy training blocks — the rodent gut data is striking enough that I'm willing to be the experiment of one."
            <span class="quote-attr">guest · biohacking podcast · 2024</span>
          </blockquote>
          <div class="read">
            <span>Self-experiment · no control</span>
            <span class="verdict">Read pattern →</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="anec-card" data-src="blog">
          <div class="src-row">
            <span class="src-ico">B</span>
            <div class="src-info">
              <span class="name">Self-experiment logs · blogs</span>
              <span class="meta">n = 19 long-form writeups · 2020–2026 · structured</span>
            </div>
            <span class="freq" data-level="rare">Rare</span>
          </div>
          <h4 class="pattern">Some bloggers report no perceptible effect even after 6+ weeks of consistent use.</h4>
          <blockquote class="quote">
            "Six weeks, daily injections, careful pain journaling. Nothing measurable. Possibly placebo failures, possibly the peptide doesn't do what people say it does."
            <span class="quote-attr">independent blog · Nov 2023</span>
          </blockquote>
          <div class="read">
            <span>Negative reports are systematically underweighted online</span>
            <span class="verdict">Read pattern →</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="anec-caveat">
        <strong>How to read this.</strong> Anecdotal reports are influenced by selection (people who try peptides and feel nothing often don't post), recall bias, placebo response, and uncontrolled stacking. Use them to generate <em>hypotheses</em>, not conclusions. Where a pattern is reported consistently across all four source types — Reddit, forum, podcast, self-experiment — we surface it in <strong>§ III Evidence-claimed benefits</strong> as "anecdotal", with the lowest dot rating.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

